HEADWORD: Talbot
<hw>Tal"bot</hw> <pr>(t⟦add⟧l"b⟦ucr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sort
of dog, noted for quick scent and eager pursuit of game.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wase (1654).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The figure of a dog is borne in the arms of the
<xex>Talbot</xex> family, whence, perhaps, the name.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Talbotype</ent>⟦br⟧
